Note: Lubricant is required for the O-rings on the CP40 nozzle holder. Before use, apply lubricant to the end of the nozzle holder and insert into every nozzle tip until the lubricant has coated the inside of the tip and the resistance decreases. Do NOT use white lithium grease for this; it can damage the O-rings.
The FTP is the Functional Test Placement. It's a PCB that's designed to test how well your machine is calibrated.
